4 HR____ MOURNING THE DEATH OF ANN NOBLES COLEMAN.
5
6 WHEREAS, the death of Mrs. Ann Nobles Coleman on
7 March 8, 2026, is noted with sadness, and her life marked by
8 grace, faith, and devotion is commended and celebrated with
9 thanksgiving; and
10 WHEREAS, Mrs. Coleman lived her life with elegance,
11 courage, and dignity, embracing fashion and personal
12 expression not merely as style, but as a reflection of her
13 strength, confidence, and individuality; and
14 WHEREAS, at an early age she professed her faith in
15 Jesus Christ and began a lifelong journey of service and
16 devotion to the Lord; and
17 WHEREAS, she was a faithful member of Orange Hill
18 Baptist Church in Grove Hill, Alabama, where she first
19 dedicated her life to Christ, and after moving to Mobile,
20 she continued her spiritual journey at Hopewell Missionary
21 Baptist Church, where she joyfully served in the choir; and
22 WHEREAS, Mrs. Coleman later became a devoted member
23 of El Bethel Primitive Baptist Church under the leadership
24 of the Reverend Dr. Jonathan L. Yates, and subsequently
25 joined her beloved husband at Bethel A.M.E. Church, where
26 she faithfully served in numerous capacities until her
27 health declined; and
28 WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her husband,
Page 1

WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her husband,
HR239 INTRODUCED
29 Howard; parents, Charlie Nobles (Ethel) and Flora Pogue
30 (John); brothers, Toles Nobles, Oneal, Frederick, Lloyd,
31 Larry, Emrol, and Joseph Pogue; sisters, J. Carolyn Shuford
32 and Erin Baldwin; brother-in-law, Milton Shuford; and
33 nephew, Jonweau; and
34 WHEREAS, left to cherish her memory are devoted
35 brothers, Melvin Pogue, Dwight Pogue, and Charlie Nobles
36 (Lesia); devoted sisters, Paulette Stokes, Valerie Cox
37 (Alphonso), and Donna Silas; sisters-in-law, Marcia and
38 Donna; and a host of devoted and loving nieces, nephews,
39 cousins, other relatives and friends; and
40 WHEREAS, Mrs. Coleman was a valuable member of her
41 community who loved her Heavenly Father and her family; she
42 formed many special friendships through the years; she will
43 be sorrowfully missed, but her influence remains, and her
44 memory will be forever treasured in the hearts of those
45 whose lives she shared; now therefore,
46 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
47 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That while mourning the death of
48 Mrs. Ann Nobles Coleman, it is comforting to remember her
49 generous and gracious life, and this resolution is offered
50 to her grieving family with heartfelt sympathy.
